# Recipe Bottle Workforce Regime — the manor's ONE workforce identity pool
# (RBSRW). There is exactly one of these per manor: the org-hosted pool founded
# once at manor setup and standing for the manor's lifetime, beneath which every
# foedus hangs as a provider (per-foedus provider trust lives in the
# rbmf_foedera library, one rbrf.env each). Pool lifecycle and foedus lifecycle
# are deliberately distinct. Carries no secrets — every value is a public
# identifier — so it ships committed.
#
# Seeded to the STANDING SPIKE TRUST's pool. The manor-setup finisher founds the
# pool from these values (ensure-exists); the pool id and org are
# pool-time-immutable (changing either founds a fresh pool), while the session
# duration reconciles (the finisher PATCHes the live pool to match).

# GCP organization numeric ID owning the workforce pool.
RBRW_ORG_ID=

# The manor's one workforce identity pool ID — org-scoped, one pool serving every
# depot under the manor; every foedus a provider beneath it. The
# principal://…/workforcePools/«id»/subject/«subject» member every admission
# grant names is formed from this id.
RBRW_WORKFORCE_POOL_ID=

# Workforce pool session duration — the sitting cap (900s–43200s). Caps the
# federated token's lifetime under either acquisition mechanism; the live window
# an interactive avowal opens.
RBRW_SESSION_DURATION=43200s

# eof
